, \"to\": 205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The giant rings were a popular addition to the monument for visitors and tourists in Paris during the July 28-August 11 Olympic Games in the French capital.\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998074145, \"rank\": 1.9252606546424052e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 349, \"end\": 355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5520815331441963, \"rank\": 0.4634007417606316, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The giant rings\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"a popular addition\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"the monument\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 263}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 276}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"-August\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo announced on Saturday that she intended to take down the originals, which are too heavy to remain on the monument, and replace them with new rings.\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hidalgo\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"the originals\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 440}, {\"ngram\": \"the monument\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"new rings\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 520}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does not seem appropriate to us that the Eiffel Tower, which has become the symbol of Paris and the whole of France since its construction 135 years ago, has the symbol of an outside organisation added to it in a permanent way, whatever its prestige,\\\" a statement from the Association of Gustave Eiffel's Descendants said.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998074145, \"rank\": 1.9252606546424052e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999832924317726, \"rank\": 1.3401129219679611e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"its construction\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 665}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"an outside organisation\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"a permanent way\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 753}, {\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"its prestige\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"the Association\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"Gustave Eiffel's Descendants\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The association's chairman Olivier Berthelot-Eiffel, a great-great-grandson of Eiffel, told AFP the family did not see any problem with the rings staying longer than the Paralympic Games which wrap up on September 8.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 1067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The association's chairman\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"Olivier Berthelot-Eiffel\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"a great-great-grandson\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"Eiffel\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 946}, {\"ngram\": \"the family\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"any problem\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 981}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 996}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But the Eiffel Tower should not become an advertising outpost.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"an advertising outpost\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne Hidalgo should have said that she wanted to keep the Olympic rings, not that she had decided it, and then discussed the idea with the Paris council and relevant individuals,\\\" he explained.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1133, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 1272, \"end\": 1277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998074145, \"rank\": 1.9252606546424052e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"relevant individuals\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Culture Minister Rachida Dati, a long-time critic and opponent of Hidalgo, also cast doubt over the idea, saying 